Here are both approaches for Shell navigation in .NET MAUI:

**1. Register the route:**
```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate with a string parameter:**
```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**3. Navigate with the full object:**
```csharp
async void OnProductTapped(Product product)
{
    var parameters = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
}
```

**4. Receive both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**
```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product { get => _product; set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // String parameter approach — value comes in as a string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service if needed
        }

        // Full object approach — value is the actual object
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**5. Wire the ViewModel to the page:**
```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| Syntax | URI query string | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| Deep-link safe | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| Passes complex data | ❌ No | ✅ Yes |
| Value in `ApplyQueryAttributes` | `string` | Original object type |

Use the string approach for simple IDs and deep-link support. Use the object dictionary when you already have the data in memory and want to avoid a redundant fetch.
